<subSubSection pageId="115" pageNumber="743" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="115.[117,1326,1943,3079]" pageId="115" pageNumber="743">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[119,474,2692,2725]" pageId="115" pageNumber="743">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List (as 1. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,421,2731,2764]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="115" pageNumber="743" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">auratus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Griffith" authorityYear="1821" box="[432,561,2731,2764]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Trachypithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="115" pageNumber="743" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mauritius">mauritius</taxonomicName>
). The West Javan Langur has been protected by Indonesian law since 1999. Although still widely distributed, its forest habitats are much reduced and fragmented due to agriculture and human settlements. The West Javan Langur is hunted for food and the pet trade. It occurs in Gunung Gede Pangrango, Gunung Halimun Salak, and Ujung Kulon national parks, Cibanteng Nature Reserve, and Cikepuh Game Reserve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
